content: I appreciate this chess app more than any other i have used. I found a "bug", reported it, and saw it remedied quickly. To the author: I wonder, is it possible for the "graphical engine evaluation display" to ALWAYS display relevant "engine result" scores? Even when the engine is outputting "threat". I also might appreciate an ability to adjust the range of the graphic itself. I would prefer a range of +/-1 to +/-9 as opposed to being locked at +/-4. I offer to pay you more for that.
replyContent: Always displaying the engine result during threat would be possible but it would mean to start the engine twice (which means doubling the CPU power needed). It's locked at +/-4 because if the display is fully white or black it means that this side should be winning. The graphical evaluation is just that - a quick overview of the winning chances.
